DataElement.preferredName: Odds Ratio Heterozygosity Standard Error java.lang.Double
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The ratio of the odds of an event occurring in one group to the odds of it occurring in another group, or to a sample-based estimate of that ratio._Having two different allelic forms of a gene, one inherited from each parent, on each of the two homologous chromosomes.:The standard deviations of the sample in a frequency distribution, obtained by dividing the standard deviation by the square root of the total number of cases in the frequency distribution._Generic value domain for a primitive java datatype that is a Double-precision floating point number (64-bit IEEE 7540).
